@startuml CU12_Sequence
!include ../_shared/global_style.iuml
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
autonumber "<b>"

title CU-12 — Consultar grafo cognitivo del estudiante: Diagrama de Secuencia
note across
    CU-12: Angular llama a AxiomEngine DIRECTAMENTE.
    Django NO participa en este caso de uso.
end note

actor Tutor as Actor
boundary "Angular\nCognitiveGraphComponent" as Angular
participant "AxiomEngine\n(Go + Fiber, port 8080)\nhandlers.go:150-186" as Handler
participant "graph/memory.go\n:188-235" as GraphEngine
participant "BAML → AWS Bedrock\n(Amazon Nova Micro)" as LLM

Actor -> Angular : Seleccionar estudiante {student_id}\ny tópicos a consultar
Angular -> Handler : GET /api/v1/tutor/student/{student_id}/cognitive-graph?topics=...

Handler -> Handler : Parse student_id from URL path\nParse topics from query params

Handler -> GraphEngine : ClassifyCognitiveGraph(student_id, topics)

GraphEngine -> GraphEngine : Subgraph extraction\nfrom knowledge graph
GraphEngine -> GraphEngine : Topological sort\nof concept dependencies

GraphEngine -> LLM : Parallel BAML fan-out\n(structured prompts)
LLM --> GraphEngine : Classification responses

GraphEngine -> GraphEngine : Merge and deduplication
GraphEngine -> GraphEngine : Hallucination validation
GraphEngine -> GraphEngine : Response enrichment

note right of GraphEngine
    Node state classification:
    - "failed": concept student did not pass
    - "learning": prerequisite of a failed concept
    - "mastered": concept student passed
end note

GraphEngine --> Handler : { nodes[], edges[] }
Handler --> Angular : HTTP 200\n{ nodes: [{ id, label, state }],\nedges: [{ source, target }] }

Angular -> Angular : Render with\nCytoscape.js / D3
Angular --> Actor : Visualizar grafo cognitivo\ncon nodos coloreados por estado

@enduml
